==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mainprise
<hw>Main"prise</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>main</ets>
hand + <ets>prise</ets> a taking, fr. <ets>prendre</ets>, p. p.
<ets>pris</ets> to take, fr. L. <ets>prehendere</ets>,
<ets>prehensum</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A writ
directed to the sheriff, commanding him to take sureties, called
<xex>mainpernors</xex>, for the prisoner's appearance, and to let him go
at large. This writ is now obsolete.</def> <au>Wharton.</au>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Deliverance of a prisoner on security for his
appearance at a day.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mainprise</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mainprise
<hw>Main"prise</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Mainprised</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Mainprising</conjf>.]</vmorph> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>To suffer to
go at large, on his finding sureties, or mainpernors, for his appearance
at a day; -- said of a prisoner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>main road</ent>⟦br⟧
